items.title: Scaevola albida
items.content_text: Unknown Scaevola species - possibly introduced - with fleshy, lightly serrated, glabrous leaves and pale blue flowers that have longer 'petals' than spp. listed for Wilsons Prom. On Tidal R. lookout track, in mixed weedy/native veg.

items.title: Sphaerolobium minus
items.content_text: 0.5m small shrub in sandy soil (full sun) by coastal track between Tidal River and Little Oberon Bay, Wilsons Prom.

items.title: Caladenia tessellata
items.content_text: The Thick-Lip Spider-orchid is a small geophytic terrestrial orchid endemic to NSW and Vic. About 19 populations are know, with about 450 plants. This one seen on LilliPilli Car Park walk from Tidal River, Wilsons Prom. It is listed as Vulnerable under EP

items.title: Olearia rugosa subsp. allenderae
items.content_text: subsp. allenderae (newly named) only occurs at Wilsons Prom. See cordate leaf base at the bottom of pic2 which is a key feature.

items.title: Thelymitra malvina
items.content_text: Along with previous observation (10253), this shows the limits of the positions where this new species record for Wilsons Prom was seen - about 6-10 plants seen on the side of the track. Plants were open in pouring rain (no sun).

items.title: Thelymitra malvina
items.content_text: New species record for Wilsons Prom. Nearest records are west of Korumburra and Providence Ponds Reserve (east of Sale). Distinctive mauve tufts on column arms. Apparently opens only in mornings. These were open in pouring rain (no sun).
